The Arab American Family Support Center (AAFSC), a nonprofit organization that supports and promotes family cohesion in the greater Los Angeles region, announced that the University of California Los Angeles (UCLA) has joined over 25 other universities nationwide in a unique project to help families of all cultures to talk about sensitive issues such as sexual abuse, date rape and dating violence in a proactive, positive and healing manner.โThe UCLA project will educate UCLA students about preventing sexual abuse and assault. This includes creating a university-wide policy on sexual assault and abuse prevention and training a new generation of men and women on what constitutes healthy relationships,โ said Saba Ahmad, executive director of AAFSC, which has a campus office on the UCLA campus.The โA Call To Menโ Project has established itself as one of the most impactful campus prevention programs in the country. Founded by AAFSC in partnership with the New York University Center for Gender and Sexuality Studies, the program has reached over 150,000 students, more than 3,000 men and women.

View this post on InstagramA man from Jaffa is in critical condition after he was shot in the head and stabbed in the stomach by two Palestinian assailants, police said Saturday. Police and rescue personnel were called to the scene near the corner of the Kikar Haim and Kfar Tavor neighborhoods of the city at around 12:40 a.m. Saturday. The wounded man was evacuated to the Sheba Medical Center in Tel Hashomer with life-threatening injuries. He is currently in serious condition in the ICU. The two suspects fled the scene on foot, police said. Police are searching for the assailants and checking to see if the incident was terror-related. The victim was a member of the ultra-Orthodox community, Haaretz reported.

What will happen when we start dying of old age at 50? Or when we lose someone to dementia before they turn 50? But, while we have made a great deal of progress in aging research and even have a few therapies that have helped some people extend their lifespan a bit, there is still much we don't know about how to slow aging. What I know is that the only thing stopping us from curing aging is that the field is not getting the funding it needs, and that it will take some brave people to make it their careers. The thing is, no one wants to become old in the first place.
